    {
      "segments": [
        {
          "scid": "sn36.26:1.1",
          "pli": "Atha kho sambahulā bhikkhū yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā … pe … ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te bhikkhū bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ: ",
          "en": "Then several mendicants went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him: "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn36.26:1.2",
          "pli": "“katamā nu kho, bhante, vedanā, katamo vedanāsamudayo, katamā vedanāsamudayagāminī paṭipadā? ",
          "en": "“Sir, what is feeling? What’s the origin of feeling? What’s the practice that leads to the origin of feeling? "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn36.26:1.3",
          "pli": "Katamo vedanānirodho, katamā vedanānirodhagāminī paṭipadā? ",
          "en": "What’s the cessation of feeling? What’s the practice that leads to the cessation of feeling? "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn36.26:1.4",
          "pli": "Ko vedanāya assādo, ko ādīnavo, kiṃ nissaraṇan”ti? ",
          "en": "And what is feeling’s gratification, drawback, and escape?” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn36.26:1.5",
          "pli": "“Tisso imā, bhikkhave, vedanā—",
          "en": "“Mendicants, there are these three feelings. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn36.26:1.6",
          "pli": "sukhā vedanā, dukkhā vedanā, adukkhamasukhā vedanā. ",
          "en": "pleasant, painful, and neutral. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn36.26:1.7",
          "pli": "Imā vuccanti, bhikkhave, vedanā. ",
          "en": "These are called feeling. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn36.26:1.8",
          "pli": "Phassasamudayā vedanāsamudayo. ",
          "en": "Feeling originates from contact. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn36.26:1.9",
          "pli": "Taṇhā vedanāsamudayagāminī paṭipadā. ",
          "en": "Craving is the practice that leads to the origin of feeling. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn36.26:1.10",
          "pli": "Phassanirodhā … pe … ",
          "en": "When contact ceases, feeling ceases. … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn36.26:1.11",
          "pli": "yo vedanāya chandarāgavinayo chandarāgappahānaṃ. Idaṃ vedanāya nissaraṇan”ti. ",
          "en": "Removing and giving up desire and greed for feeling: this is its escape.” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn36.26:1.12",
          "pli": "Chaṭṭhaṃ. ",
          "en": ""
        }
      ],
